<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-52-0217 </DOCNO><TEXT>This paper reviews problems with the current Surface Mining Control andReclamation Act (PL 95-87) in regards to fish and wildlife managementpractices. It reviews the provisions for fish and wildlife managementprovided for in the law, but ignored by the regulatory authorities andthe coal industry. It discusses the benefits to be gained by using variousgrass and tree species while leaving water impoundments for fish habitatand recreation. Recommendations are provided for developing a useablemanagement plan.</TEXT></DOC>